  "title": "A2A Allocates EUR7 Billion for Decarbonization Efforts | MarketScreener",
  "text": "A2A S.p.A. 0.00% (Alliance News) - A2A has unveiled its first climate transition plan, committing EUR7 billion by 2035 to key decarbonization initiatives: expanding renewable energy, enhancing energy efficiency, waste valorization, and extending district heating networks.\nAs reported by Milano Finanza on Thursday, the document outlines the objectives, tools, and operational levers that will steer the Lombardy-based multi-utility towards achieving Net Zero by 2050.\n\"This plan reflects our commitment to a decarbonized future,\" stated CEO Renato Mazzoncini, noting that the company's 2035 industrial plan foresees EUR23 billion in investments, of which EUR17 billion are aligned with EU taxonomy and EUR7 billion are dedicated to CO 2 reduction.\nOf this amount, EUR3.4 billion will be allocated to the development of renewables, and EUR1 billion to CO 2 capture technologies, heat recovery for district heating, electrification of the waste collection fleet, and bioenergy.\nBy Giuseppe Fabio Ciccomascolo, Alliance News senior reporter\nComments and questions: redazione@alliancenews.com\nCopyright 2025 Alliance News IS Italian Service Ltd. All rights reserved.\nÂ© Alliance News - 2025",
